---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="CV" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <!-- PROFILE -->
  <section class="mb-10 border-b border-base-300 pb-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Anh Bui</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold text-base-content/90">
      Senior / Lead Software Engineer · .NET, Azure, Fintech & Payments
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-base-content/65">Based in the United Kingdom</p>
    <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-x-4 gap-y-2 text-sm">
      <a
        href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/btanh/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer"
        class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary"
      >
        LinkedIn
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/AnhBuiDeveloper"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer"
        class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary"
      >
        GitHub
      </a>
      <a
        href="mailto:anh.bui@anhbui.dev"
        class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary"
      >
        anh.bui@anhbui.dev
      </a>
      <a
        href="mailto:btanh82@gmail.com"
        class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary"
      >
        btanh82@gmail.com
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SUMMARY -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Professional Summary</h2>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-base-content/90">
      Senior <strong>.NET Engineer</strong> with more than <strong
        >20 years of software engineering experience</strong
      > building and supporting business-critical systems. My recent work
      focuses on <strong>fintech, payment platforms, distributed systems</strong>,
      and <strong>reliable Azure cloud services</strong>.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-4 text-base-content/75 leading-relaxed">
      I enjoy turning complicated operational problems into software that is
      secure, observable, and straightforward to support. I am comfortable
      modernising long-lived systems incrementally, bridging legacy platforms
      with modern cloud services while keeping production stable. Alongside my
      professional engineering work, I design, build, and operate a growing
      portfolio of SaaS products used by real browser users.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- EXPERIENCE -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Experience</h2>

    <div class="time-line-container grid gap-6">
      <TimeLineElement
        title="Independent SaaS Product Builder"
        subtitle="Personal products · Active development and operation"
      >
        <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-base-content/85 grid gap-1">
          <li>
            Designed, built, and operate <strong>seven live SaaS products</strong>
            for practical browser workflows, with free and Pro capabilities.
          </li>
          <li>
            Developed Chrome, Edge, and Chromium extensions covering capture
            tools, audio processing, connectivity monitoring, AI conversation
            export, and browser privacy automation.
          </li>
          <li>
            Own the complete product lifecycle: discovery, UX decisions,
            implementation, licensing, device activation, release management,
            privacy-conscious design, and customer support.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="Senior Software Engineer"
        subtitle="Aryza · Sep 2022 – Present · Birmingham, United Kingdom"
      >
        <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-base-content/85 grid gap-1">
          <li>
            Work on a large-scale loan management and fintech platform,
            supporting the full loan lifecycle and multiple third-party
            integrations.
          </li>
          <li>
            Build secure, resilient .NET services integrating with credit
            agencies, fraud and identity providers, and payment gateways.
          </li>
          <li>
            Deliver payment flows including hosted checkout, card tokenisation,
            3-D Secure, asynchronous callbacks, and webhook-driven processing.
          </li>
          <li>
            Design Azure-based solutions with App Services, Azure Functions,
            Queue Storage, Azure SQL, Application Insights, and Key Vault.
          </li>
          <li>
            Apply resilience patterns including retries, circuit breakers, and
            idempotency while bridging legacy VB6 systems with modern .NET
            services.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="Senior Software Engineer / Software Engineer"
        subtitle="Pinewood Technologies · Jul 2017 – Aug 2022 · Birmingham, United Kingdom"
      >
        <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-base-content/85 grid gap-1">
          <li>
            Progressed from Software Engineer to Senior Software Engineer,
            working with C#, .NET Core, and ASP.NET Core.
          </li>
          <li>
            Built and maintained production software in a long-running
            enterprise product environment.
          </li>
          <li>
            Contributed to design decisions, feature delivery, troubleshooting,
            and continuous improvement as responsibilities grew.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="Software Engineering Manager / Engineering Leadership"
        subtitle="AS White Global · 2013 – Jun 2017 · Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam"
      >
        <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-base-content/85 grid gap-1">
          <li>
            Progressed into engineering management, with the manager role held
            from Jan 2017 to Jun 2017.
          </li>
          <li>
            Oversaw hiring, training, and management of engineering teams with a
            headcount of up to 17.
          </li>
          <li>
            Worked with engineers to define project scope, timelines, budgets,
            and technical requirements while promoting quality and continuous
            improvement.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="Senior Software Engineer"
        subtitle="Harvey Nash · Sep 2012 – Aug 2013 · Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam"
      >
        <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-base-content/85 grid gap-1">
          <li>
            Developed browser-based applications and delivered software from
            design specifications through testing and technical documentation.
          </li>
          <li>
            Reviewed client requests, supported bug resolution, contributed to
            architecture decisions, and researched solutions for difficult
            technical problems.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="Senior .NET Developer and SD Team Leader"
        subtitle="Easy IT Solutions Vietnam · Apr 2007 – Aug 2012 · Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam"
      >
        <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-base-content/85 grid gap-1">
          <li>
            Built .NET applications and developed the technical leadership
            foundation used throughout later senior and management roles.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </TimeLineElement>

      <TimeLineElement
        title="Programmer Analyst"
        subtitle="Jabil Circuit · Nov 2009 – Mar 2010 · Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam"
      >
        <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-base-content/85 grid gap-1">
          <li>
            Contributed to software analysis and delivery in a manufacturing
            environment.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </TimeLineElement>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- EDUCATION -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Education</h2>

    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-base-content/85">
      <li>
        Bachelor’s Degree in Information Technology / Computer Science
        <span class="text-base-content/65">(details available in full CV)</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- CERTIFICATES -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Certificates</h2>

    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-base-content/85">
      <li>Microsoft .NET related certifications (historical)</li>
      <li>Agile / Scrum training and certifications</li>
      <li>Ongoing self-directed learning in cloud and system design</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- SKILLS -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Skills</h2>

    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 grid gap-2 text-base-content/85">
      <li>
        <strong>Languages & Frameworks:</strong> C#, .NET Framework, .NET Core,
        ASP.NET Core, Web API
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Fintech & Payments:</strong> hosted checkout, tokenisation, 3DS, payment
        callbacks, reconciliation
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Integrations:</strong> REST, SOAP/WCF, FTP/SFTP/WebDAV, secure authentication
        (OAuth2, Bearer, Basic)
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Cloud & Azure:</strong> Azure Functions, Queue Storage, App Services,
        Azure SQL, Key Vault, Application Insights, Azure DevOps
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Product Engineering:</strong> SaaS products, Chrome and Edge extensions,
        licensing, device activation, release management, customer support
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Reliability:</strong> retries, circuit breaker, idempotency, logging,
        monitoring, alerting
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Architecture & Practices:</strong> distributed systems, microservices,
        software architecture, code reviews, mentoring, incremental modernisation
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- RECOMMENDATIONS -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Recommendations</h2>
    <p class="text-base-content/75 leading-relaxed">
      Read recommendations from colleagues and managers who have worked with
      me across software engineering and technical leadership roles.
    </p>
    <a
      href="/recommendations"
      class="mt-4 inline-block text-sm underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary"
    >
      View recommendations
    </a>
  </section>

  <!-- FOOTER CTA -->
  <section>
    <p class="text-base-content/75">
      This web CV is a concise overview.
      View my
      <a
        href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/btanh/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer"
        class="underline hover:text-primary"
      >
        LinkedIn profile
      </a>
      or contact me at
      <a href="mailto:anh.bui@anhbui.dev" class="underline hover:text-primary">
        anh.bui@anhbui.dev
      </a>
      or
      <a href="mailto:btanh82@gmail.com" class="underline hover:text-primary">
        btanh82@gmail.com
      </a>
      to request a detailed CV or discuss opportunities.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
